ERROR IN COMPILER GUIDE
Section 17.2:
	1. it says to use the -W flag to compile PM applications.
	This is false, do *NOT* use -W for PM applications.
	Using it will case the ZW?.LIB files to be linked in instead
	of the OS/2 libraries.
	2. If a function is declared as _pascal, it needs to appear
	in upper case in the EXPORTS list in the .DEF file. If you
	do not link with case sensitivity, /NOI, then it is not
	necessary. An alternative method is to declare the exported
	functions with the _export keyword.
	3. ZTC does pass the .DEF file to BLINK.
	4. The -b is no longer necessary, as it is now the default.
Section 17.3.3
	Remove the -W flag from the makefile ZTCPM.MAK.
